<paragraph blockId="53.[151,1437,150,1833]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,349,402,428]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Recognition.</emphasis>
This species is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Burington, 2022" authorityName="Burington" authorityYear="2022" box="[709,786,403,428]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Eucelatoria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[709,786,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">E. sica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[794,885,403,429]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[794,885,403,429]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Burington, 2022" authorityName="Burington" authorityYear="2022" box="[941,1032,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Eucelatoria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kopis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[941,1032,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">E. kopis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1040,1131,403,429]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1040,1131,403,429]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, as all have two presutural and one postsutural thoracic vitta, black palpi, and tomentum covering the apical third of the scutellum. It differs in that the parafacial tomentum is gray.
</paragraph>
